examples.en: She pushed him away.
I am sick of being pushed about.
I am pushed for money, deadly.
She's always pushed for time.
He pushed for a leaner military.
examples.ru: Он выступал за сокращение численности вооружённых сил.

examples.en: Life pushed him hardly.
He pushed his horse on.
He pushed her very hard.
examples.ru: Он очень сильно её толкнул. / Он очень грубо её отымел. (сленг)

examples.en: The crowd pushed forward.
I slowly pushed the door open.
He slowly pushed the door open.
He pushed me into the table.
He pushed her out of the way.
examples.ru: Он оттолкнул её в сторону /с дороги/.

examples.en: She pushed her way to the front.
He pushed the throttle backward.
I pushed open the unwilling door.
examples.ru: Я с трудом открыл тугую дверь.

examples.en: He pushed the table into a corner.
Philip pushed him towards the door.
The liberal party pushed for reforms
We pushed deep into enemy territory.
He pushed her to finish her doctorate.
He pushed the bill in the legislature.
examples.ru: Он упорно продвигал законопроект в совете штата.

examples.en: She ran to him, but he pushed her away.
examples.ru: Она подбежала к нему, но он её оттолкнул.

examples.en: She pushed back her chair and stood up.
My husband pushed me into leaving the job.
Poverty pushed them to the breaking point.
She pushed him in and told him not to move.
examples.ru: Она впихнула его внутрь и приказала не двигаться.

examples.en: Dad pushed off and jumped into the rowboat.
examples.ru: Папа оттолкнулся от берега и запрыгнул в лодку.

examples.en: The door didn't move, so she pushed harder.
examples.ru: Поскольку дверь не тронулась с места, она толкнула посильнее.

examples.en: She pushed her wet hair back from her face.
examples.ru: Она отбросила с лица мокрые волосы.
